=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_BrownNoise_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex characteristics, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 0.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0000
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0000
  pitch_clarity: 35.7177
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -20.2567
  resonance_freq: 193.7988

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: BrownNoise Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/BrownNoise.html
// Tags: BrownNoise, Classes, noise
